    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Great complaint here because nothing heard for a month from missionaries
                            at Marash, Hadjin, Aintab, Bitlis, Harpoot, Marsovan, Cæsarea. What, if
                            anything, do you hear as to their safety and general condition? Does
                            Government interceptor prevent missionaries communicating with their
                            friends or with you?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
